{
  "text": "Importantly, the two methods should be used at the same spatial scale, considering samples at distances not greater than ca. 0.56 /\u221a2 , where \u03bc is the mutation rate of the loci considered 80 (Rousset 2004) . Because the regression method based upon groups can be applied in a continuous population, some empirical case studies compared the results provided by the two methods with the 82 same species in the same population [CITATION_1] Suni & Gordon 2010; [CITATION_2] ).",
